                            <comment id="425383" author="adilger" created="Thu, 22 Aug 2024 00:39:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There are also several other OBD_FAIL cases listed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10363&quot; title=&quot;some fail_locs set on client but checked on server&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-10363&quot;&gt;LU-10363&lt;/a&gt; that are set on the client and checked on the server, but I haven&apos;t looked if they overlap with the test cases here. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="425382" author="adilger" created="Thu, 22 Aug 2024 00:36:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/56113&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/56113&lt;/a&gt; &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12567&quot; title=&quot;ha-all-ior-ssf-fpp-mdtest: IOR fpp: cannot close file. ERROR: Input/output error&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-12567&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-12567&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; ptlrpc: handle reply and resend reorder&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; is fixing sanity.sh test_224 which was setting &lt;tt&gt;fail_loc=OBD_FAIL_PTLRPC_CLIENT_BULK_CB=0x515&lt;/tt&gt; on the client and checking it in the OST target code. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="370412" author="adilger" created="Tue, 25 Apr 2023 00:33:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The sanity.sh test_119d subtest is removed via patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/50731&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/50731&lt;/a&gt; &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13706&quot; title=&quot;sanity test_119d: the read rpcs have not completed in 2s&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13706&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-13706&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tests: remove test 119d&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
